National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice met with President Catherine Samba-Panza of the Central African Republic to congratulate her and the country on the peaceful national elections and upcoming conclusion of the transitional period. Rice commended Samba-Panza for her leadership and progress towards peace and reconciliation. Both leaders emphasized the importance of an inclusive government that represents the diversity of the Central African Republic. They also expressed concern about reports of sexual exploitation and abuse by UN peacekeeping forces and supported swift accountability. Rice reiterated that the United States will remain a committed friend and partner to the Central African Republic.